tune.ComposerNotes:
in Allen Carden's The Missouri Harmony, 1820;
    atrib. to Ananias Davisson (1780-1857) in his The Kentucky
    Harmony, 4th ed., 1821.

attrib. to L.M. Smith; tune related to Bourbon;
    in Wyeth's Repository of Sacred Music, by John Wyeth
    (1770-1858), 1810.

in Simon Browne's A Sett of Tunes, c.1720;
    attrib. to Browne (1680-1732) in Wyeth's Repository of Sacred
    Music, by John Wyeth (1770-1858), 1810.

in Allen Carden's The Missouri Harmony, 1820;
    attrib. to A. Chapin in Church and Sunday School
    Hymnal.

var. attrib. to Chapin, Boyd, and Western
    Melody; in Alexander Johnson's Tennessee Harmony, 1818;
    according to Southern Harmony, by Chapin.

in Joseph Funk's Harmonia Sacra, 15th ed., 1876;
    full Tune name: Chorus Anthem: Praise the God of
    Israel.

in Joseph Funk's Harmonia Sacra, 5th ed., 1851;
    full tune name: ""Anthem. The Earth is the Lord's. 24th
    Psalm.""

in Joseph Funk's Harmonia Sacra, 10th ed., 1860;
    attrib. to H. S. Rees in Elder H. C. Cayce's The Good Old
    Songs.

in Joseph Funk's Harmonia Sacra, 12th ed., 1867;
    full tune name: ""I have set Watchmen upon thy
    Walls"".

in Alexander Johnson's Tennessee Harmony, 1818;
    attrib. to Austin in William Walker's Southern Harmony,
    1835.
